This is consistent on my machine which is running Redhat Linux 9.0.
I have installed the 2.1 release for linux-motif load on this machine.

To create the problem, following the below steps:

1. create a new project XYZ;
2. add external jar file say /usr/local/bin/abc.jar;
3. press ok;
4. close the project XYZ;
5. open the project XYZ;
6. select properties;
7. select java build path;
8. add external jar file say /usr/local/bin/pqr.jar;
9. press ok;
10. press ok to close properties;
11. < at this moment the error dialog will be displayed
"An error occured while setting the build path.
 Reason:  resource /usr does not exist"
> 
12. press cancel to close the properties dialog.
